caption.text:
I've finally finished my quest! 😁 22 Super Mario games completed, played in chronological order with the original software and hardware like Nintendo intended. What a ride!
~
I started this because as a big fan of Mario games there was quite a few I hadn't completed or even played! I also wanted to find out which game out of the whole series was my favourite. Was there a game I hadn't played which would be my new all time favourite? What's my least favourite? How have the games evolved over time? These were the questions I wanted to find out.
~
I've compiled my list, ranking all 22 games from best to worst, based on how much fun I had playing each one. I'll post the list shortly - it'll be interesting to see where your favourite game ranks!

5 MELHORES GAMES DE CORRIDA PARA CELULAR

E muitos são de graça.

Jogar games de corrida no celular é muito bom. Você tem diversas opções de títulos, desde os mais voltados para a simulação até algo mais voltado para a diversão, no melhor estilo kart. E o sucesso recente de Mario Kart Tour não nos deixa mentir.

O Painel do Gamer indica cinco games de corrida incríveis para você jogar no celular. Confira nossa lista:

1. Mario Kart Tour
Mario Kart chegou para celulares quebrando recordes de download e trazendo toda a essência do game que amamos nos consoles. Você pode participar de torneios, fazer bastante drift e usar os itens que atrapalham bastante os seus adversários. A promessa é que você vai ter muitas atualizações com novidades e, quem quiser, pode pagar para ter acesso a mais bônus, mas o game é gratuito. Baixe no iOS e Android.

2. Horizon Chase
Um dos games brasileiros de maior sucesso dos últimos anos ganhou uma versão para PS4, mas tudo começou nos celulares. O game é pago, mas você pode correr no primeiro mapa gratuitamente. Baixe para iOS e Android.

3. Garena Speed Drifters
O Garena é conhecido por Free Fire, mas Speed Drifters está fazendo grande sucesso, principalmente no Brasil. O game é acessível para jogar e você pode ainda personalizar bastante elementos como personagem e veículos. Baixe para Android e iOS.

4. Starlit On Wheels
O game do estúdio gaúcho Rockhead Games é muito divertido ao seguir a fórmula de kart e ser bastante acessível. Você tem diversos personagens para escolher e muitas pistas para correr e, o mais legal, é poder construir e compartilhar seus circuitos para compartilhar com a comunidade. Baixe de graça para Android e iOS.

5. Real Racing 3
Quem deseja jogar um game mais focado na simulação tem o que há de melhor nos celulares com a série Real Racing. Ele é tipo um Forza Motorsport ou um Gran Turismo nos celulares, apresentando carros reais de diversas fabricantes e muitas pistas. Baixe no iOS e Android gratuitamente.

caption.text:
FOLLOW: @GameFacts 🎮

CONT’D: Via GameSpot “Our AI now has a new state of awareness between complete awareness of your position and totally unaware of where you are," The Last of Us Part II co-director Anthony Newman said in an interview with GameSpot. "We sometimes call that vague knowledge." For example, even if you were to stealthily take down an enemy with a silent weapon -such as a bow or pistol with a silencer attached to it--another enemy can still find the body, look at where the arrow or bullet is lodged in their comrade, and infer in which direction they were attacked. ℹ️

MY TAKE: Well that’s awesome. Looks like I have to buy the game now, although probably a good idea I complete the first one first. 🤗

QUESTION: What do you think of this news? Will you be buying it? 🤔

Ontem um dos muitos spinoffs de Kingdom Hearts comemorou seu décimo aniversário de chegada as Américas. Em 29 de setembro de 2009, nosso lado do mundo recebeu Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days para o Nintendo DS. Esse jogo que poucas pessoas sabem pronunciar o nome certo mostra a história de Roxas enquanto trabalhava para Organization XIII, com seus eventos ocorrendo entre o Kingdom Hearts e Kingdom Hearts 2, incluindo também Chain of Memories (outro spinoff que ainda não foi citado aqui). 358/2 Days é, na minha opinião, o que traz a história mais pesada e tapa vários buracos que haviam na trama. O jogo foi transformado em um filme com as cutscenes e está disponível nas coletâneas de PS3 e PS4. Para quem quiser jogar no DS, eu recomendo pela história, pois o gameplay é um pouco maçante.

caption.text:
#Nintendo ha annunciato in queste ore l'arrivo di un titolo totalmente inatteso: Trattasi di #BrainTraining per #NintendoSwitch!

Questo nuovo capitolo del gioco curato dal Dr Kawashima, arriverà per ora esclusivamente in Giappone il 27 dicembre e proporrà alcune features inedite come: Il multiplayer locale/online, alcuni minigiochi che sfrutteranno la porta infrarossi del #JoyCon ma anche dei report che verranno inviati regolarmente allo smartphone.

Il gioco fisico includerà in terra nipponica una stilo dedicata (ufficiale Nintendo) che aiuterà gli utenti a scrivere sullo schermo di Nintendo #Switch, che in questo titolo si utilizzerà prevalentemente in verticale. Che ne pensate? 😮

Non amo essere eccessivamente sentimentale, ma si, vi voglio davvero bene! Mancate già ❤️

Got out my #handhelds today for a good cleaning 🧼🎮 I’ve always been a fan of gaming on the go, it changes the experience in so many ways for me. Still missing a #gamegear and a #neogeo pocket, I sold them like a moron when I was in my 20’s 😑 also a wonderswan would be a nice addition. What’s your favorite handheld and why? I personally love the 3DS games, but prefer the feel of the vita. The switch is a hybrid so I guess it doesn’t really count. Let me know what you guys think!!!! caption.text: Frente a frente. Dos versiones con diferentes filosofías. Después de unos días con #switchlite he podido percibir cosas interesantes. La primera de todas, redescubrir el buen hacer de Nintendo con el primer modelo. Materiales más premium que el modelo Lite,  y una pantalla que se hace aún más grande, después de jugar a la Lite. De ahí, la diferencia de precio. Switch Lite, es más plástico, pero muy agradable al tacto, y sobretodo, ligero. Es lo más sorprendente, apenas notamos su peso. Su tamaño es el ideal para llevar en el bolsillo pequeño de la mochila, algo que suelo hacer con mis 3DS. La cruceta le sienta genial y jugar a juegos 2D es una delicia. Para los juegos de lucha, no es precisión absoluta, pero se puede jugar bastante bien. Destacaría sobretodo, su comodidad para jugar, más ergonomica que el modelo original, por su tamaño y peso. Creo que es la evolución lógica de 3DS, una portátil potente con una gran pantalla, que me trae recuerdos de otra gran portátil; la mítica PSP. Quizás Switch Lite, es el resultado de la evolución de las portátiles, la representante de un legado, que ha cobrado forma en un dispositivo que se acerca mucho a la consola portátil perfecta. PS Vita estuvo cerca de esa perfección. Recomendaría Switch Lite a todos aquellos que siguen usando su 3DS, y quieran seguir usando consolas portátiles. Fue diseñada para ocupar un sitio en tus pertenencias diarias. Y para los que tenéis el modelo original, quizás solo exista un motivo para que os penséis su adquisición.... #nintendoswitch #nintendoswitchlite #nintendo #nintendoswitchneon #brummelgames #gamer #games #videogames #retrogamer #nin10do #videojuegos

Here’s my #StackItUp for September! 
The two Club Penguin DS games were a couple of games I loved playing when I was younger.  I’m glad I was able to buy them back and for a good price 😉 (both CIB for $7 total)
GameStop prices their preowned games the same, regardless of what case they come in.  So, when I saw Shadow of the Tomb Raider in the steel book for a good price, I couldn’t pass it up ☺️ It’s a game I want to play, but will probably stay in the bottom of the backlog. 
I wasn’t sure if I was going to buy Borderlands 3 or not because I’m not big on FPS.  However, when I watched some streams of it, I caved and bought it!  I’m currently level 10 in the game so I’m not super far into it. 
Link’s Awakening I knew was a must-buy from the moment it was announced.  BoTW was the first Zelda game I really played and I’m anxious play through all of them 💚 I already finished the game and I 100%’d it EXCLUDING the Dampé stuff
The SNES game bundle of Dr Mario & Tetris was something I randomly stumbled upon in GameStop.  I was surprised to see a boxed SNES game and picked it up since it was in wonderful condition.  The box is a tiny bit beat up, but everything inside is in mint condition.
And that’s what I got this month!  There are a lot of games releasing in October that I want, but I’m going to try and only buy a few of them 🙈

🇬🇧 This new Super NES controllers are so cute! They are now available for Nintendo Switch Online users on the official Nintendo website.
🇮🇹 Questi nuovi controller del Super NES sono così carini! Sono ora disponibili per gli utenti Nintendo Switch Online sul sito ufficiale Nintendo.

caption.text:
Some freehand sketches I did today and yesterday 
For the second one I first drew my Switch from the back. I came up with the layer idea after I finished the outline. All of the pencil stuff are the elements on the side / front that can’t be seen from my perspective so it was pretty tricky. The purple pen stuff comprises the manufacturing text, the logo, and the other kickstand mode. Probably should’ve included the sliders for the controller somehow.

El Nintendo Switch Lite se ha convertido en la segunda consola revisada más vendida de todos los tiempos en Japón, con un total de 177,936 unidades vendidas en su primera semana de lanzamiento en esa región.

Esto se compara a las 187,480 unidades que se vendieron para la consola revisada más vendida en ese país en su primera semana, titulo que lo posee actualmente el Nintendo 3DS XL, y las 171,925 unidades que vendió el Nintendo DSi en su lanzamiento.

Dicho esto, el Switch Lite ha sobrepasado otras consolas populares de Nintendo que recibieron revisiones, como lo es el New Nintendo 3DS XL, Game Boy Color, Game Boy Advance SP, y más.

Esto estaba de esperarse, pues la semana pasada el Switch Lite ya había alcanzado 114,00 ventas en tan solo 3 días, dándole días de resta para que alcanzara las 170k, adicional a la inclinación de Japón por consolas portátiles y videojuegos móviles.

El modelo original del Nintendo Switch, por su lado, ha alcanzado 9 millones de ventas de unidades, con 52,000 de ellas a penas siendo de la semana pasada.

El Nintendo Switch Lite ya se encuentra disponible en tiendas.

caption.text:
Pokémon: Let's Go Eevee (Switch) 
Pokémon has a universal appeal, but I think I'm about 20 years too old to be the target audience for this entry in the franchise.
Credit where credit is due, this remake of the first generation games excels in presentation. The game oozes charm, and is just how you'd picture the first games when you played them as a child: from the updated visuals and cutscenes, to the adorable interactions with your titular partner Pokémon, to your team following you outside their Pokéballs. Also a fun idea is that a second player can drop in and play co-op, with everything turning into a double battle. 
However, it feels like this game targets three demographics: those who have not played Pokémon since the first generation, those whose only experience with Pokémon is Pokémon Go, and very young children. Pokémon is not too complex of a game to begin with, but Let's Go is oversimplified to the point where it just stops being fun. Wild Pokémon encounters work just like Pokémon Go (except the wild Pokémon can flee at any moment), and battles are heavily weighed in the player's favour (I constantly found that my team was landing critical hits, dodging attacks, and enduring fatal blows, with flavour text saying it was because they didn't want me to be sad). I beat the game with zero effort using an underleveled team.
Another gripe I have is that we have explored Kanto in four different generations before even counting Let's Go. There is nothing new to see, no new area to explore, and as only the original 151 Pokémon are in the game (and also Meltan), I was hard-pressed to use Pokémon I had not previously had on my team in other games.
Similarly to the game itself, the Pokéball controller that came with the game is more style than substance. It's definitely a neat idea, and I did feel it improved the catching aspect as the motion controls felt more natural with a ball in hand, but the joystick also being the A button led to mis-selections as my attempt to click the button also moved the cursor.
Overall, I would only recommend this to people new to the Pokémon series, or who have not played since the original Game Boy games.
5.5/10

caption.text:
▪︎Gear of the week # 31
▪︎Gear # 31.1 submitted by @lullaby.vs and # 31.2 by @bygraciechan
▪︎
▪︎
▪︎Polls for gear of the month start now in my stories and end on 3rd October.
▪︎
▪︎
■ Please note that the gear shown in gear of the week/month isn't expected to be good in battles! The gear is usually just kinda good looking and has some pure abilities. Sometimes I just pick a random weapons that suits with the gear but not the abilities. So please don't judge that the gear isn't good for battles, thanks. ■
▪︎
▪︎
▪︎
■ How to participate in gear of the week: ■
▪︎
▪︎Gear set is supposed to have pure/perfect abilities, however, the main ability doesn't have to be the same as the sub abilities (but would be better :3).
▪︎Gear dodoesn't have to be good in battles. The gear is supposed to look good, for example the separate gear parts have the same color or style.
▪︎You can participate more than once.
▪︎Just dm me a picture of your gear and its abilities, you can get the picture with the Nintendo Switch Online App. You don't have to take pictures of the gear with an amiibo like I do them in my posts because I'll take the pictures myself.
▪︎
▪︎At the end of every month the gear of the week will participate in polls where people can vote for the gear of the month.
▪︎
#splatoon #splatoon2 #nintendo #nintendoswitch
